        <h4 align = "center"> <text class = "text-uria"> Uria: </text> Uranism </h4>
        <p align = "justify"> When Kaus started to grow, he had a lot of influence on other peoples of Vernesis. And the one who drank the most from its source was Uria; absorbing a lot of your religion. Uranism is a “Manichaean Australism”. </p>
        <p align = "justify"> While the Kaoans believe in a vast pantheon of 11 major gods and many minor gods, all with their important roles and none in fact evil - reflecting Kaus' dubious morality - the Urians, already accustomed to the concept of the struggle between good and evil, order and disorder, etc., saw in Ura the god they needed and, in Iorte, the god they hated. </p>
        <p align = "justify"> It took a few centuries to bring about the emergence of Uranism, not as an aspect, but as a separate religion. Where Ura is the supreme god, omnipresent and omniscient, protecting humanity and fighting Iorte, the demon-jackal, wicked and treacherous. </p>
        <p align = "justify"> This clearly reflected the political situation of the two peoples, who have been at war ever since. Kaus wants all the power of the stars, and will do anything to conquer him - including attacking Ura constantly -, Ura wants to extinguish the evil and meanness of the world - and what better way to start than to destroy the city that has the same personality and symbol of the most wicked of demons. </p>
        
